reviews: I booked two superior rooms however was allocated two classic rooms on arrival. when I queried this at checkin i was told we had two good classic rooms on a high floor. This is not what I booked & paid for - I was told to take it up with the booking company ( Stayforlong) . I have repeatedly done so since my return but they have not even acknowledged my email. Overall positives about the hotel - very good location, rooms are bright, breakfast has a very good range of food on offer. My review is based on my experience and this was a disappointment due to the rooms we were allocated. We had specifically paid more for the superior rooms as we were celebrating a 25th wedding anniversary. I think the hotel could have done more to sort this out by allocating us what we had paid for or refunding the difference.

The hotel is wonderful, the rooms are quite small but that's to be expected in Paris; however, our room was very clean, and the bed was quite comfortable. We traveled with our two young children and the king sized bed was very lovely, the sofa bed not quite though our kids didn't have any complaints.

The location is very good, only a few blocks from multiple metro stations so it is very conveniently located. There are also good bakeries and restaurants with half a mile walking distance. The area also felt safe, and it was really nice and quiet at night, our sleep was never interrupted.

I've buried the lede enough; let's talk about the amazing customer service at this hotel! First of all, Deborah at the reception is an absolute angel. Our daughter fell ill with an ear infection while we were there and Deborah found us a doctor that spoke English and would be able to see us on the same day, she did some other additional things that really cheered our daughter up (I'll keep them to myself because I don't want to create unreasonable expectations for others). To say that Deborah went above and beyond is an understatement, she single handedly ensured that we stay at this hotel again next time we are in Paris.

The rest of the stuff is also wonderful, from the person that made us coffee in the mornings at the hotel cafe, to the rest of the reception staff that while obviously very busy still found time to call us a taxi and give us directions with a smile. The room team also didn't disappoint, we didn't even have to request that they made the sofa into a bed; they noticed we had kids with us when we left the hotel to explore the city and when we got back that night the sofa bed was made and ready for our kids to sleep in.

Deborah and the rest of the Novotel team really enhanced our Paris experience, we are very grateful to them for it and can't wait to go back!

the hotel is below average for family category rooms.... the rooms are too small for a international traveller with luggage it is evan difficult to walk inside the room. Room have no ventilations & the staff do not cooperate to evan switchon cetralized AC of the hotel. hot water is also not available at night times & brekfast was also average. not at all value for money.

Excellent hotel in a great location near to public transport and / or within walking distance of many places, restaurants, bars etc but still pretty quiet.. very friendly staff and a very clean hotel.. didnt eat here but the bar had all the drinks youd normally want and prices pretty similar to anywhere else in Paris.. wed definitely stay here again if / when we are back in Paris, a city we loved. A special note too, the hotel made a great gesture for us as it was our first visit to Paris.. very much appreciated..

This was a great hotel conveniently located near the Montparnasse Gare in Paris. Our rooms were clean and the beds were very comfortable. The staff provided excellent customer service. We enjoyed breakfast onsite which offered a wide assortment of choices, including fresh fruit and pastries.

Just returned from spending a few days in Montparnasse with friends for my 40th birthday - and this was my first stay at the this particular Novotel.

Pros
- Hotel super clean in all areas and a real focus on keeping everything nice and tidy.
- The staff on reception are super friendly and made a real effort to talk to me like a real person and a valued customer.
- The hotel has made real attempts to be environmentally friendly and eco conscious.
- The room itself was well thought out in terms of plug sockets, USB chargers and wifi and the bathroom toiletries are nice.
- Hotel iron wasn't great (not sure why they don't have irons with steam / water in them).
- Good location for Montparnasse and well connected to Public transport (see note below)

CONS
As usual - there are a few small touches which sometimes miss the mark for me, and they're annoying niggles but woreth pointing out.
- The Novotel showers in Paris are a poor design. the shower trays are super shallow and this meant the bathroom got very wet.
- Housekeeping staff don't really pay attention to DND signs and enter rooms very quickly after knocking. This woke me up a few times.
- Breakfast was poor. Noisy, crowded, a poor food offering and too many people in the restaurant (including loads of screaming badly behaved kids) - the food itself wasn't worth the 19 fee - so this was a bit disappointing.

Jutst a navigation tip - the hotel is in a bit of a quiet part of Montparnasse, and can be quite tricky to find - it's also in an area that can be quite desolate at night tuckerd away at the back of the station. I never felt unsafe but worth bearing in mind if you're our late at night. I went to a nearby supermarket which was a bit of a walk, and felt a bit sketchy.

Overall would come back - and thanks again to the reception staff for making me feel welcome.

We stayed family 3 for two nites .
Staff welcomed as cane in clean and quirky reception room clean and spacious for family 3 . Quite too Breakfast perfect . This was a package holiday with breakfast.
Bar attender Aurelien was so friendly polite and made us feel very comfortable. He happily helped and served us exactly what we wanted perfect .
As for two members of staff nikolos and a woman not !!
The other lady well she tried her best which I told her to one side and thanked . The issue was we had paid for breakfast both days however we were getting taxi at 6am breakfast 6.30am so I asked for some pastries she scoured face and said no ! ? So I asked her why she said not open till 6.30 am fair enough but surely they prepare earlier so I asked for refund ! No !! So really it didnt matter what ever I said she was not going to go above and beyond like the bar attender had . Also nikolos said over top of her no its just fruit and small cake they could offer !! Well as far as Im concerned no help no emotion nor compassion it will be long day travelling home yet nothing to offer organ fruit !! Well I would like a response from management as I did not get my fulfilment of what I had purchased for which was bed and breakfast two days .
I will rate lower which is a shame as it was perfect highly recommend before this but wanted all to know not everyone is nice or obliging.

I really enjoyed our stay here. We booked online with TripAdviser and I was happy with the price. It wasn't close to major attractions, but Uber rides were around 13 euros to get to Louvre, Eiffel tower, and PSG stadium. Close to metros and main bus lines too. Several highly rated restaurants were within walking distance, and so we did.

Great hotel, great location.
Was walking distance to the Montparasse Tower - which is well worth a visit.
Walking distance to the Eiffel Tower although we only done this once as we got day tickets for the metro line which meant you could hop on and off all day around Paris. Its worth buying a day ticket if you want to see lots of sites as there are lots of metro stations dotted around.
Breakfast had a varied selection and catered well for families.
The staff were very friendly and nothing was too much trouble.
We didnt have a great view and the room was fairly small for a family but nonetheless was clean.
My only complaint would be that the coffee and milk wasnt replenished at all. Im sure I could have gone to reception to ask for some.

All in all a fantastic a hotel and would stay again.

Great room, with a view of the Tower from the eighth floor. Comfortable bed, good shower, and breakfast was fabulous - even almond and soy milk for the lactophobic..
Immediate access to Gare Montparnasse just outside the hotel, although it is a 5-10 minute walk to the main platforms. Great stay.

This hotel amazing, staff excelente, always great customer service, in my opinion good customer service is not in England, not even a greeting, everything tidy and can expect the best from all staff, always very helpful, could visit here again, it's very very fantastic.

The front desk, Mahmoud was super to check in with, very accommodating and great service
The hotel staff was very friendly and did a great job, from the concierge to restaurant staff

The room had a very comfortable bed and a nicely renovated bathroom. Room carpet needs to be replaced with laminate, same goes for the restaurant carpet.
Breakfast buffet had a variety of choices

Walking distance to the Louvre and Notre Dame. Lots of restaurants and cafes around hotel

Booked the executive room apparently gave us the classic room spoke to the manager and she still insist it the executive room far from what its showing in the website. I would not recommend to anyone its more like a scam. You can get better room for way better price around.

On June 16, 2022, my firm used Booking.com to reserve the Novotel Paris Gare de Montpareese in Paris. The stay was pre-paid. Upon arrival the hotel staff required our employee to provide their own credit card and charged the entire stay on their card. Now we have paid twice and cannot get the hotel to respond to our requests to refund. They have hung up on us. Nice place, cannot recommend staying here when they charge double.

Great! Good location. Friendly service. Nice restaurants in the area. "Walking" distance to Eiffeltower.
One block from Paris Metro and railway station. Parking in the hotel garage. Rooms were nice and the team managed to get 3 adjacent rooms for our family trip

Manager Lionel and his staff provided an enjoyable lunch for our tour group which included fresh salmon and vegetables and Tiramisu dessert with one birthday candle and the staff took the time to wish me a happy day. We will return in the future to enjoy more of the facilities due to the central location in Paris at the rail station.

Good value for money. Novotel provided complimentary minibar top-ups daily, service staff was helpful and prompt (i.e., delivery of in-room fan when we felt that the A/C is not strong enough, preparation of stool in toilet for young children)

Room is spacious enough for a family of 4 (2 Adults + 2 children - with sofa bed). Serves pretty good food at the attached hotel restaurant (Halle Quatre).

We had a great experience in this hotel. The area was fine we took taxis to the major sights and this was easy enough. Once in the centre centre we walked from place to place.

All the staff very friendly and helpful. Breakfast was a great selection. The only thing that was missing for me was some vegetables, like tomato or cucumber. Other than that selection was great.

We actually ate dinner in the hotel and it was amazing. The kids menu is fantastic value too. Definitely recommend having an easy meal there.

The room was clean a bit small and some paint was chipping on the toilet door but it was clean and I think thats the most important. We managed a family of 4 in the standard room.

I would definitely stay again. It was good value for money.

Thank you!

Hotel very very clean.
Easy check in/out - nice staff
Good breakfast - a little busy. A large selection of foods and drinks.
Location good- we walked to Eiffel Tower with young kids .
Also very easy to get taxis.

Good and friendly staff. Very helpful. Easy check in and check out. Location is quite good, close to metro and bus stations. Rooms size is quite decent and neatly maintained. Hotel rooms in Paris are quite small anyways. Only criticism would be cleanliness. The reception/bar/breakfast area and rooms could be cleaner.

2nd Novotel on recent visit and 2nd poor experience. Worst aspect was breakfast. Overcrowded due to limited time slot, stuffy room and no COVID measures being taken at all. Hot food was either burnt or uncooked. If was going to get ill on trip, it would be here. Rude male staff member on arrival seeming to object to our arrival time (2nd female staff member was lovely though). 2 towels for family of 4. Tired room. Comfy bed and great location were redeeming features.

Ive just checked out of this hotel after 4 nights, the family room we stayed in was great, so happy that our beds and room were cleaned up for us each day, the location is great 30min walk to Eiffel Tower and 5 min walk to train station. Will definitely stay here again. Staff are lovely and really helpful, Great touch with the photo machine and balloon guy at breakfast. Thank you !

We'll be coming back for sure! We stayed here in March 2022 for 4 nights with a child and a teenager. Fabulous stay overall. Based on our experience, I have no hesitation in recommending this hotel if you are coming to Paris. We would definitely return here again with the kids. They really loved it too.
Would highly recommend it for a number of reasons.....
1. Ease - effortless check-in and check-out.
2. Clean - Spotlessly clean in all communal areas and in the room. This is to be noted, as it's busy but was always really clean and tidy.
3. Good food - plenty for breakfast. Ate dinner one night, all enjoyed it.
4. Extras - Little added extras that the kids loved: a passport photo machine to take selfies (and you can stick up your photo on their hotel reception wall) and one morning there was a guy making free balloon creations for kids too!
5. Quiet room - no noise. General area is quiet too.
6. This is probably one of the most important for me - the hotel room had a superbly comfortable mattress! I had a great sleep in a family room!
7. Every day - The daily room clean was one of the best I've ever seen......spotless every day (thank you!), with added extras like a personalised note on arrival, chocolates, daily bottles of water in the fridge.
8. Location - near loads of good restaurants, shops, pharmacies (max. 5 min walk). We walked from the hotel every day to the Louvre, Eiffel Tower, Arc de Triomphe (approx. 30 minutes brisk walk to each but very straight forward). Hotel is in a very central location to everything.
10. Staff - really friendly and helpful staff...all that we encountered could speak English too which was a great help for us when making enquiries re: restaurant bookings, local attractions, etc. And a special thanks to the housekeeping staff for cleanliness/tidyness.
11. Space for a family in a family room! In- the ground floor and first floor have various "chill out" zones/areas.....so if you want a quiet coffee, to browse the internet or read a book there's loads of alternative spaces to sit too (not just hotel room). This is a bonus for a family with a teenager as sometimes a family room can seem small/crowded, but not in this hotel as there's loads of other different areas for all to use too when relaxing.

Our stay was so amazing. The staff was friendly and kind. The service was amazing. The food, delicious. The bar, one of a kind. It was also really nice to speak with Maria, a restaurant staff, she was so kind. It was very nice to speak russian with her. It made our stay so much more comfertable. The staff really made the stay so pleasant.

The rooms were beautiful and clean. The rooms were serviced everyday without having to ask. Clean towels were provided everyday and sheets changed everyday. Complimentary Minibar restocked everyday. The view was nice.

The lobby so unique and beautiful. The bar located in the lobby with a great cocktail menu. Photos of previous residents on the bar wall. So unique.

In all, I would love to come back here again, or even visit another novotel in another contry. The stay was truley exeptional! Well done!

Family of 4, we stayed one night in December. Enjoyed the hotel. Clean room. We were on the 3rd floor and it was very quiet. Didnt hear a thing from neighboring rooms. Breakfast was varied and tasty in the morning. Would definitely stay again.

We asked separate beds for 2 nights the beds were made like it was a double bed, unacceptable. The 2nd time we had to ask for the correct sheets (Monday night) and as the reception stated no service was available we had to change and make up the beds ourselves. Also we left some papers related to our voyage on a table which were thrown away. Also own shower cap + handtowel were removed from the room. The shower door is not fully extended leaving an opening resulting in very wet bathroom floor we had to continuously clean. Also toilet paper lacking last day..

As a family we had a great time at this hotel ,it was clean ,comfortable, close enough to go anywhere in Paris with a lots of transport close by
The food was very good and the staff where very professional and very kind especially the gentleman called DJAMEL ,he was very professional and very helpful ,always smiling and very kind ,he did all his best to make our stay a good experience, thank you dear DJAMEL you are a star ,keep the good work ,will defently come back

We chose this hotel for its accommodation for a family of four, with two young daughters of 12 and 14. The room given was spotlessly clean, with the sofa turned into two comfy single beds with nice pillows and matress.
Also for its location in Necker/Falguire residential neighbourhoods, where districts 6, 14 and 15 meets each other. Lots of restaurants/cafs/boulangeries/pattiseries/brasseries nearby. Also many small supermarkets, pharmacies and services (rent-a-car, etc).
The hotel is 7 mins walk from two Metro stations: Pasteur (Green 6 and 12 lines) and Gat (light blue line 13). It also has ebikes and electric scooters parkings in front of the main entrance and in many of the surrounding corners. They're a fantastic way of transport.
Last but not least, the hotel is just three blocks away from Gare Montparnasse, with connecting railways to almost anywhere, including the TER/N lines to Chteau De Versailles in 14 (!!) minutes non-stop.
As for the service, it was brilliant in all the sense of the word. I had to receive a package coming from the UK that was already waiting for me in the room the night we checked-in. The staff at the front desk was immensely gentile and helpful all the time, addressing each one of our requirements with diligence and good mood/attitude.
Breakfast was fantastic. An abundant buffet in a large salon with an open cuisine attended by a chef providing special preparations like eggs and such. Plenty of pastries and bread varieties, gluten-free madeleines, two Melitta automatic coffee makers, bacon, fresh fruits salads, cheeses, jam, french marmalades, you name it...
Beds and pillows were extremely comfortable, and noise isolation in the rooms was absolutely perfect.

We spent 11 nights in this hotel and we are absolutely grateful for the special care we received as a family group. Novotel Paris Centre Gare Montparnasse is a team effort. Each one of its members is a highly committed person trying to do its job the best way they can. Merci beaucoup Elise, Emmanuel, Alex and Alexandra, Chloe, Mairie and each one of you that made us feel like home in this wonderful place.
We're looking forward to visit you again!

The only issue we had was finding the reception area. Looked more like going into a cafe when we entered and reception could be on another floor. It was on the ground floor but behind us as we entered. Other than that, the stay was good.

It is my second stay in this hotel. It has been upgraded, is in very good shape and very well located. Unbeatable quality - price and service. Just one thing that could improve, I booked an executive room, which included minibar and nespresso, where there was literally one bottle of water, one cola and one orange juice for the whole stay, so not even a chance of choosing two people the same drink, and same think for the nespresso capsules. I guess it makes sense from a waste point of view, it is a courtesy, not a drink buffet, but I found it quite short. Staff were friendly and helpful all through the stay, very efficient with check in and check out. Will certainly repeat when in Paris.

Well located close to the train station of Montparnasse and to the metro stations. This hotel is clean and comfortable. The breakfast is great. The staff is friendly. For Paris the price is acceptable

6 of Ilya stated here for a flying visit to Paris. You can walk to the Eiffel Tower from the hotel. Rooms were very clean and prices were good. Bathrooms fantastic and shower was absolutely amazing, a full rain shower. Large plasma screen tv also. The hotel is opposite the Train Station also.
We arrived late and even though the restaurant was just closing they served us. We all had burgers and while a little rare, they were gorgeous. The staff were really friendly and welcoming. We would definitely return.

Great hotel, located in a nice area of Paris. Only a five minute walk to a metro station and a train station.

Modern reception, nice employees, rooms ok. We missed some closets to put our clothes in, but that is the only thing we missed in this hotel.

We would recommend and stay here again.

I was invited by French friends who chose this hotel located near the train station, I really appreciated the welcome, the location of the hotel, the comfort of my room, the excellent breakfast, the quality of the cleaning, the fast wifi connection, I will try to return with my wife

I had a course to go to in Paris and I went to eat at the restaurant of the Novotel Gare Montparnasse ,I had a very good experience,the food was very nice and I was served by a member of staff called DJAMEL, a very kind gentleman and he helped me to choose my food ,he is very professional,thank you DJAMEL for giving me a good experience ,I will come back and have that delicious burger again ,definitely advise any one who want have a good food and professional staff to go to this hotel.

Well situated, close to the Montparnasse train station, this is comfotable hotel. The rooms are clean and modern, the staff is friendly and the breakfast abundant. For Paris standards, the place is not overly expensive either.

We chose the Novotel hotel for our 4 day trip in Paris and everything was so great. The accommodation was very clean and comfortable. For our family of 4, it is so idealistically big enough. The care of the hotel staff is also moving. They helped us quickly with each of our requests in a very polite manner. The hotel has a great location too, from which we can see Eiffel tower. We really recommend this hotel.

Our stay was made comfortable, enjoyable and happy by excellent staff. Djamel and Camille were exceptionally helpful for us novice travellers in Paris, as were all others at the hotel. Halle Quatre provided great breakfasts and excellent meals. We enjoyed the very best G&Ts made by hotel staff, and a wonderful selection of French wines. The room was clean, well appointed and very comfortable. We will stay again and are happy to provide the highest recommendation for Novotel Gare Montparnasse.

We recently stayed at the Novotel for our stay in Paris and visit to Disneyland Paris.

The room was spacious enough but there was very little space to hang clothes. We could not hang 2 adult and 2 childrens winter coats.

The hotel is fairly central to lots of cafes, bars, shops and bakerys.

The hotel is a good 20 - 30 min walk from several metros stops enabling you to travel around Paris fairly easily. It was tricky with cases and tired children. We are seasoned travelers too.

You can see the Effiel Tower from the end of the street and from the 8th floor of the hotel. It is also an easy 20 - 40 min walk to the tower from the hotel.

If returning to Paris we would not choose it again as it was not close enough to the metro stations.

I Loved the stay
You get excellent value for your money at this hotel. The room does not have a single unnecessary square centimeter, and few frills. But it was perfect for a good night sleep. It was my second stay, and if I need a place in Paris, I'll stay there again.

Hotel has great location, super customer service, great Brkfst and late night coffee. Short walk to the Pasteur Metro and right next to gare montparnasse. Suggest to get a room in the front to avoid noise in the rear. Highly recommend local restaurant Caf templier a few steps away, best kept secret in Montparnasse.

We very much enjoyed our stay at Novotel Paris Centre Gare Montparnasse. All the staff were kind and attentive, and the breakfast is a feast! The hotel is about a 30-minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. And there are many restaurants, cafes, shops, etc. surrounding it. The hotel is very clean and contemporary. Our only issue was that our TV wouldn't allow for English subtitles. But since we watched very little TV while there, we didn't complain.

My wife and I went with another couple for vacation. Right off the bat, our rooms werent ready on time so we left our luggage at the hotel and came back later. The check-in process feels a bit disorganized with the check-in desk being two high tops near the entrance.

The other thing is that the hotel caters to families with kids and I wish we had known that before booking. We couldnt really have a relaxing drink at the bar since kids were running around shouting throughout the stay. If you are looking for a relaxing place to stay on your trip to Paris, look elsewhere.

the Hotel had a good vibe about it with nice furnishings and it was clean. I enjoyed the breakfast and the photo machine. The hotel was in a good area of Paris to walk to major attractions. With its height it was easily recognizable in the city.

This hotel is currently under renovation which is well needed!
It looks tired although in a very good location central to main attractions of Paris.
Very friendly staff whom where helpful.
Bedrooms clean and tidy although seemed to be very warm even with the heating off.
Would recommend as a cheap base just really used for sleeping.
Im sure once the hotel has finished being renovated it will be of a much better standard
If your looking for somewhere basic and clean in a good location this is the hotel for you.
No frills classic 3 star we would say.

This is our 1st trip to Paris and I am glad that I chose this hotel which had great reviews. The location of this hotel is not bad. Accessible to transportation-bus stops and metro stops (although public transportation is on strike at this moment which I believe is over a month now.) Either you walk or take the Uber. Distance to Central Paris is not bad. About 15 to 20 minutes by Uber to go to Eiffel Tower. Give some time to get to places.

The food selection at the restaurant is good too. The breakfast buffet has a good selection of food to choose from.

Hotel rooms and bathrooms are very clean and you could hardly hear noise of your neighbor. Staff are very nice and helpful.

Surrounding areas has plenty of restaurants to choose from. Maybe about 3 blocks or a 5-minute walk.

Thank you!!!!!

I was in this hotel and found the service poor ... especially the Manager Dominique ... I was mistreated ... never came back, I was devastated ... it was my worst christmas
I'm sad to have stayed me
I'll never be back

The room was too small and they didnt clean the room well when we left for the day, even the towels werent changed, the staff werent helpful at all when we tried to ask them for help for a taxi! The location is great and the breakfast is good. But I dont recommend this hotel If youre looking for a more friendly helpful environment

Picked Novotel because we had recently had another good experience with the hotel chain and we like the standard they have. not super luxury but good 4 star hotel. Room modern and good bathroom. Not a noisy room and only noise bothered us was the bathroom noise of guests above us with toilet usage in middle of night.
Breakfast wa snot included for us but we used it one time and good but can get better for this price outside hotel.

Great location. Great for exploring and walking around the centre of Paris, 30 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower.(you can see from a distance one road away from the hotel)
15 minute on the metro to Arc de Triomphe.

We spent 2 nights at the Novotel Centre Paris Montparnasse in November 2019. Contemporary and modern lounge/bar area with friendly front of house staff. The rooms are clean, spacious, bath and shower also with a separate toilet.

We stayed at this hotel for 4 nights, part of Euro trip to celebrate our 10 year wedding anniversary. Easy check in and out, with helpful staff. Our room (Executive Room with double bed) is spacious by Paris standard, with complimentary mini bar and high speed internet. Location wise is close to the Gare Montparnasse, hence easy public transport. Nearby charming local residential area with local cafes dotted around. A good and comfy stay overall!

Cheers
Crespo & Sarah

Loved our stay here!! Pretty accessible to most parts of the city!!!
The buffet breakfast is good. Rooms comfortable. It's a cute hotel with a coffee shop. Nice restaurants and cafes in the vicinity as well.

The hotel was great nice location and a great view of the Eiffel tower from our room. The staff ensured we had everything we needed and check in and check out went smoothly. overall the stay was enjoyable and i would come back again.

I'll for sure recommend this hotel
The stay was AWESOME the staff at reception lady how did my check in don't no her name but Mr and Ms Marius and Laura was so helpful. Restaurant for breakfast and bar is really nice with people like Ain Sabrina and Alexandra all staff was so helpful and they made my stay more than awesome.
Hope I'll visit this hotel again.

We stayed at Novotel Paris Centre Gare Montparnese during our time in Paris. We had a good experience although check-in wasn't as smooth but the overall experience was pretty good.

We had booked a classic room but had requested for a room with Eiffel tower view. Being an Accor Plus Member definitely pays off as we got the upgrade and a room with direct view of Eiffel.

Regarding booking, we never realized booking in Paris is gonna be such a huge task since we read reviews that rooms are expensive, small, staff is rude etc etc. After few weeks of research, Novotel fitted our requirements perfectly. We booked directly from the Accor app and were also able to use the rewards points for payment which gave us 40 euro discount!

Check-in: While we got confirmation on Eiffel tower view room 4 days before our stay, we were told early check-in is only subject to availability which is fair. We reached the hotel at 11 am and we were room isn't ready and we'll get the desired room only at 2 pm. So we decided to best utilize the time by visiting Arc de Troimphe. We were back by 2 15 pm and lady at the front desk who had assured us that room would be ready by 2 pm told that there was a misunderstanding and room still isn't ready and we had to wait for 30 mins. Now this was really frustrating because you wouldn't want to waste time in Paris for check in especially when we had Eiffel tour booked at 4 30 pm. Nonetheless after speaking to the manager and explaining him the situation we did get the room by 3 pm. But check-in experience was really not one of the best experiences of our stays with Accor hotels!

Rooms - Considering the reviews on TA about rooms in Paris, this a sufficiently big room and we got room 815 which had lovely Eiffel views! Bed was also really comfortable and we thoroughly enjoyed the stay.

Breakfast was healthy and had decent vegan options. Considering we follow strict Jain diet, we got good options for the breakfast on both days!

Room service could definitely improve since we had asked for extra towels couple of times but we never got them.

Also during our first day of the stay, there was a protest right outside the hotel against Novotel. The noise of the protest was really troubling. Wonder what the issue was about. Thankfully we weren't staying longer on first day and weren't disturbed a lot. But it would definitely affect people staying on front side of the road.

Accessibility of hotel is really convenient. We came from Gare Du Nord. Best option is to take Pasteur metro station for all the travel!

We definitely enjoyed the stay and would for sure consider it during our next stay in Paris!

We had bookings from 8-10 Nov. We had requested and got confirmation for the Eiffel view room a week before our stay. Today we arrived at 11 and they said that early check in is not available, which is ok. We spent our 3 hours out and when we came back at 2.15, the room was still not ready for check-in. The official time of check-in is 2pm and even at 2.46pm they need more 30 mins to make the room. All they have to arrogantly say is that if you want that room, you have to wait. I don't see any reason to wait beyond the official check-in time. Not at all professional. If you are crunched with time and have to make the most of time in Paris, this is definitely not the hotel you should stay at.

Well I read some reviews before I came that were saying this hotel wasnt pleasant.
Honestly from the moment we entered untill we checked out it was nothing but positive.
We stayed in a Queen room travailing as a party of 4 (myself and 11 year old daughter and my friend and her son same age)
The reception is amongst a bar/bistro was very welcoming and given it was past 10pm we were still greeted with a friendly and helpful staff.

Our room on the 7th floor was spacious, spotless clean and had some extras we wasnt expecting in the form of the children having sweets and a Eiffel Tower keyring on there bed and the adults robe and slippers. The mini bar was free and stocked with branded drinks of water, cola and juices. Again a lovely touch.

Location wise it was a 42 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower on the maps app on our phone. Although a pleasant and straightforward walk if you have mobility issues like me once you do the walk n sightsee its hard. Taxi to it was 15 euro.

We used the Metro from CDG airport it was very straightforward and took us to a stop that was 15 mins from the hotel again a very straight walk.

We had breakfast on the second day for the 4 of us it was 36 euro and it was a buffet style. Having 2 fussy kids we were amazed the amount of choice and filled up everything was fresh and tasty and the kids were made up as a Magician was around doing tricks! There was a free photo booth to take holiday selfies and print them off there too. We had room service too one night of pizza and few drinks. Again we didnt feel over charged and food was good, hot and fresh.

All the staff encountered were friendly and helpful we had a great 2 night stay. Would definitely recommend!

To use the metro from the airport it was 20+ euros and a taxi was 50 hope this helps!

If your concept of a Four Star Hotel is to be greeted at a Reception Desk by smiling staff, a Porter to take your luggage to your room and a Concierge to help you - then you will not get these services at this Hotel. One of the Male Managers was very rude about our booking, which had been made and paid for three months earlier.
The Foyer is a cross between a Delicatessen and a Bar Brasserie.
The Hotel is some distance from The Metro Station which would be a problem with heavy luggage.
Only stay here is under 40 years of age.

The staff at this hotel are awful. Rude, sullen and unhelpful. Reception area looks makeshift. Breakfast was a joke. Insufficient tables and ran out of cutlery and glasses and napkins and pastries. Cook your own eggs?!! Not value for money. Better to eat breakfast out. Worst novotel I've stayed in. Will return to Paris but not to this hotel due to awful staff. Location is not bad and rooms are clean.

The hotel is lovely and modern. Decently close to a metro station, although it's a bit of a walk down a hill. The thing that made this hotel worth it for us, was the breakfast. It was huge and delicious. We traveled with our 3 yr old, and the hotel room had a step stool in the bathroom and even offered a stroller and other baby amenities. We would definitely stay here or with this company of hotels again.

Contemporary and exceptionally clean. We made this hotel our anchor for four full days in Paris. The hotel is clean and comfortable with a great staff. Easy access to the Metro and buses! Great restaurants in the area too. Would recommend this hotel to anyone.

The hotel was pleasant, contemporary. We had some issues with the taxis in Paris and there are several Novotels so make sure youre clear to the driver which one youre staying at. We got dropped off at the wrong one and the hotel said we couldnt use their shuttle to get to the correct one so we had to grab another cab. Our fault

This is a great hotel, very clean and very efficient. The staff at reception, the bar and the dining area were all very friendly and helpful. The room (executive) was excellent. One slight issue we had - our shower door leaked water over the bathroom area of the bedroom. But, a few towels sorted that! The breakfast is excellent too. Overall a very modern, quirky but comfortable hotel with great staff in a very convenient location. Highly recommend.

Decent sized room for a Paris hotel. What I like about it is that it has a separate room for toilet. This means no rush for bathroom.
The lobby shares an area with a co-work space and there are plenty of tables and work benches around.
A convenient location in the heart of montparnasse.

Air conditioning broken - delivered warm air instead of cold. Could not turn off!! Horrible.
Fire-door just outside the room every time somebody walked passed and the door closed with a loud sound and the entire bed was shaking. Could not sleep.
Glass piece on top of the desk broken with a very sharp edge  Somebody f.ex. a child could get seriously hurt.
Shower doors stuck nearly impossible to close.
Shower-head gives so little water it takes forever to shower
Soap dispenser in shower broken, not working.
Room much too small for a four-star hotel, there wasn't even room to open our suitcase.
GOT INSECT BITTEN!
Room 406. Terrible, terrible room!!!
Only good things are location and newspaper in the lobby.

Modern hotel, with perfect styled and equipped rooms. No outside noice comes to your room. Modern reception, but with only two operators this can create waiting time.
Breakfast was complete and as expected at Novotel. Location near station perfect and only ca. 5-10 minutes walk from metro.
Hotel has bar in reception area
For me as business traveller this was a good choice !

Just stayed one night but really enjoyed the whole experience. Very seamless checkin, great modern comfortable room for 4, delicious dinner downstairs, friendly staff, sumptuous buffet breakfast, free late checkout on sundays. Location is very central with quick access to metro and train. Would go back in a blink!

Great location and a comfortable place. The rooms included an iron/board, a coffee maker, a refrigerator, and a safe. There are many restaurants nearby.
There is a separate tub and shower.
The internet is free and works well.

We had another very easy check-in and once again was provided with a room upgrade, it does pay to be a Accor Le Club Member. Our room was on the 8th floor, 817 with a view directly to the Eiffel Tower, it was clean, spacious and the bed was very comfortable. We enjoyed the hospitatilty of the staff at the Bar and Restaurant. It was very easy to get to the Paris Metro line and the there are some very nice places to eat close to the hotel. We enjoyed our stay and would deffinately stay here again.

I stayed 6 nights with my family, location is really good and safe, it is also very clean a bit pricey though. The breakfast in the morning is extremely busy so try and get there before 8am if you can, good experience overall.

We just finished a wonderful stay at Novotel Gare and stayed in room 819 this week at the hotel. It is a great location that was less than a 10 minute walk from the train station. Beautiful room that had a view of the Eiffel Tower which was especially awesome at night when it was lit up. Breakfast was superb with lots of choices. Many pastries including chocolate croissants, juices, fresh coffee and a hot food station for waffles crepes and you could also cook up your own fresh eggs to go along with the bacon, sausages and beans.

The service at the bar provided by Adele was awesome. We ended up sitting right at the bar and had such a great time chatting with her that we came back the next night as well. We normally skip the hotel bars but she was so awesome that we had to come back. She was humorous and provided just the right amount of banter. It was also nice that she knew so much about our home in Canada. She is a beautiful person inside and outside who is an awesome addition to the hotel.

She had lots of advise on what to do in both Paris and SW France. We took her advise and visited Cognac after we left Paris. So historical with great places to sit down for a drink on numerous terraces after we did a Cognac tour.

All in all a great hotel with an awesome bartender that we will be sure to use on our next trip through Paris.

Our visit was first after checking changes,find it interesting concept but not sure if busload turist will check in?Overall we liked this place due to location and parking.
There should be information about short cut to Gare.

Although our family holidays were not supposed to be in this hotel, it was finally and certainly out best stay so far in Paris.
From the reception (Emmanuel, Amy and team) to the bar (Camille, Amaury and team) through the restaurant, it was all about smile, good vibes, welcoming, good food, good ambiance !!!
Rooms were clean and service was top!
We strongly recommend this hotel for every family stat in Paris.
Bravo guys!!!!!

A very clean and modern hotel about a 10-min walk to Pasteur metro or Gare Montparnasse. My family was given two mid-sized adjacent rooms but not connecting despite repeated requests before and during our 7-night stay. Wi-fi worked great. WC or toilet was in a separate room from the sink and shower. Showers were weak, not particularly hot, and leaky (on the floor). Sinks were super shallow without a soap dish.

Hotel caters to family as evidenced by the somewhat chaotic breakfast buffet. Lots of variety with good selection of fruits. A good start to our day. Rooms were surprisingly quiet. And clean -- we saw a carpet cleaning crew. But be careful of their card keys -- they tend to erase when near metro cards or cell phones.

This place tries to be hip and young and while there are lots of families with kids as I sit in the lounge theyre playing vulgar rap music. Housekeeping is spotty. We returned at 3pm and the room wasnt done again. Half an hour later she knocked, not announcing herself, then rolled her eyes when I said we needed five minutes to wash up and leave. Had breakfast here once as its crowded and busy. Wont be staying here again.

The bar staff were excellent, especially Adle whose attention to detail results in the best gin and tonics and a great guest experience!

A whole-hearted thank you to the entire team who made my stay a memorable experience.

812

A nice hotel and a nice room! that's about it

Had to wait nearly an hour after scheduled check-in time for my room to be allotted. We were asked to busy ourselves in the other rooms (we had 4 rooms totally for 3 nights!), when my room was allotted. I was expected to go down to the reception to collect my key!
What happened to courtesy of coming over to give the key or an apology for the inconvenience?

Found a piece of steel scrub in our scrambled egg! when we told the staff - "let me check" - comes back after 10 min - "sorry about that"

Would this be the response to any guest or is this type of response reserved for Indians?

Day of checkout, we leave luggage in the lobby to finish breakfast, Person at the reception shouts out rudely
Staff - I am not responsible if you lose your luggage
Me - I haven't placed it outside the hotel on the pedestrian path for someone to cart if off, its inside the hotel
Staff - I am not responsible
Me - Then what are you responsible for
Staff - My desk
Me - Ok. move the luggage to the restaurant

Btw, I did notice that other guests did leave their luggage at the very same place and other reception staff didn't have such statements to make to them (of course, those guests were not from India)

Is this how guests are treated at this hotel?

If the reception staff is responsible only for his/her desk
Who is responsible for the steel scrub in the scrambled egg?
Who would be responsible for the delayed room allocation?

We stayed as a family with 11 & 12 yr old boys . The hotel is in a great location close to metro & restaurants. Stayed for 3 nights . Staff were helpful . Secure baggage store on day of check out that was very helpful . Didnt eat there . Lovely spacious clean room . V small criticism the toilet was separate from bathroom , great but no sink in toilet so you still had to go in bathroom to wash yr hands . We all had a great stay !!!

We stayed 5 nights in this hotel which is located quite far away from metro station/actual platform 20 mins walk.
To compensate location, rooms are clean and nicely decorated with modern facilities, a bit small for 3 persons... but this is Paris.
Buffet is great and offer an extremely wide choices, with quality bread and vienoiseries.
Every two days, a magician or balloon twister comes to entertain kids. The hotel also offers activities for kids and adults making the lobby always happening and busy.
Lastly staff are friendly and well versed in English.

A very beautiful hotel in the center of Paris and very close to everything. We stayed there for one night before we travel to Costa Rica and that was great. The room was judge, clean and very well decorated . Great stay.

This is a good and convenient, if slightly boring choice when travelling with children. The rooms, although on the small side, are not a bad size by Parisian standards. There is enough room to accommodate two extra childrens beds which the hotel will arrange for no extra cost.
Rooms are clean without much character.
A plentiful and good quality buffet breakfast costs 18 per adult but again, children eat for free.

Travel tips - from Gare Montparnasse, follow signs to Gare Vaugirard. The Novotel is next door. There is a taxi rank round the back of the hotel serving Gare Vaugirard SNCF station. The most convenient metro stations are Pasteur and Gait. Use these rather than Montparnasse Bienvenue which is further and much more complex.

We used this hotel as a base for 3 days in Paris before the start of a Globus tour. The location was good, as were the rooms and breakfast. Use the Pasteur metro stop nearby to go anywhere in the city.

Staff are helpful. We were allowed to check in half an hour earlier. Quiet location with main train station to Vasaillies and Bordeaux within 5 minutes walk. Breakfast is great.The room is rather small for a family of four.

The hotel was recently renovated and is quite nice. Staff is very friendly and helpful, the restaurant is also good, both for breakfast and dinner. A big plus for us was that they had free strollers available.

The street itself is not very charming and Montparnasse or Pasteur stations are a 5-10m walk away. That would be my biggest criticism though, apart from that it is a very good place to stay.

We really liked the feel of this hotel. we were lucky enough to be upgraded to a superior room with a balcony - we could even see the top of the Eiffel Tower.
Room was a good size with very comfy bed and a good double sized shower.Being a superior room there was even a complimentary mini bar with water, soft drinks and chocolates The staff were very friendly and efficient, and everywhere in the hotel spotlessly clean. The bar area was OK but very expensive - escecially as the Euro was so strong against the pound when we visited Paris.
Its a few steps from the nearest Metro but we felt safe in the area - there are lots of bars and cafes close by.
We didn't have breakfast in the hotel but ate outside one of the cafes on a typical leafy Parisian street and watched the world go by - excellent.
A good place to stay - only a few stops on the Metro from the main city sights (watch out for pick-pockets on the Metro) and the area of Montparnasse is vibrant and buzzing - recommended.

This hotel is very big largest rooms are available in this hotel and biggest swimming pools are available in this hotel and eating foods are great quality and have a very delicious and very tasty.this hotel give best service.

My experience at Novotel was great.Check in was fast.The rooms had a weird configuration where the actual toilet was around the corner from the sink. Other than that everything was fine ,good location, good food,and nice clean rooms..

Forgot to book a large bed so given a room with 2 singles and they are small (I am a normal BMI adult and almost fell out several times in night).
So very tired.
Food very good albeit limited choice
Service very good
Bathroom weird - toilet quite removed from sink and shower
I would t stay again but cause sleep is important for me. Am sure if you have a proper double or larger bed your sleep will be fine

The hotel is in a good location around a busy area (you just need to walk around to explore it), room was a bit small for a family of four however this was expected for a room in Paris. Service was very good, staff were friendly and helpful. Overall it was a good and satisfying stay

This hotel was really nice overall but they location was really bad. One hour from Charles De gaulle airport and pretty far from most of the attractions. However, it is really close to the train station. They had a nice buffet breakfast and they treated us nicely.

The location is a bit further than I had thought from Montparnasse and the hotel tries to give a trendy loft style (at least on the ground floor). The rooms are not quite as modern as the photos suggest but are functional. Air conditioning works well which was a relief. Unlikely I will return, mainly due to the location. I found the cost a bit high , given the location

Our complimentary breakfast was delicious. Staff was kind and helpful. Our beds were comfortable and our room was cool. Was a ten minute walk to the Metro from where we embarked on all our sightseeing destinations.

If I could give 0 stars, I would. Staff completely unhelpful. Booked this room as the hotel boasts having air conditioning in all rooms. Got a room that is over 85 degrees inside for me, my husband and 2 kids (one who is asthmatic). The temperature outside is over 95 degrees so opening a window is not an option. Told the staff the issue upon check in at 3:30 and said they would send someone. Got back to room at 11:30 pm, no one came by and when we went back down, only option was to wait till the next day to see if anything became available but no promises could be made in respect. We had to beg for a fan which they finally gave us begrudgingly and did nothing to cool it down and was extremely loud!
While I am not French, I do understand quite a bit and had to hear them ridicule me as I walked away for being American! Ridiculous and completely blown away that a hotel treats guests this way.

Arriving from airport taxi driver told me I cannot drop you in front of the entrance of your hotel so i had to walk almost 500 meters with my luggage uphill to the hotel and it was the same when I checked out

This was a comfortable hotel in Montparnasse not to far from the Montparnasse Tower. The room was nice and the bathroom had amenities. The air conditioning was on and the room was comfortably cool. It was quiet at night so we were able to sleep well.
The breakfast was really good, with a large variety of hot and cold items.
There were many restaurants and shops nearby.

We got the train from St Malo to Paris. The train stopped at Gare Montparnasse which is opposite the Novotel Hotel. The Eiffel Tower is immediately visible when you step into the street which was a great delight. It is about a 20 minute pleasant walk to the Eiffel Tower. It is a very central hotel which is quiet at night, well sound proofed (I am very particular about noise). We had a family room which consisted of a double bed and a double sofa bed. Hadn't come across one of these before but it basically converts to 2 single beds which are completely separate, similar to 2 camp beds. It was perfect for my 2 children, age 10 and 11. Breakfast was great. There is a great sports bar downstairs, the hotel had a nice ambience with friendly staff. I would definitely recommend for a family break. Clean, bright and modern.

First time to a Novotel and very impressed. Staff good, hotel good, food good and good value so good all round. Busy as you would expect for a budget hotel close to the Eiffel Tower. All round great experience in Paris. Well done Novotel

We booked the hotel for the last night of our France vacation. We arrived early from the champagne region and this is what went on:
10am - we were told that the hotel was overbooked and that they had rooms available, offered a room at a different hotel. Mind you, we were early there so they couldve given un any room. We declined, spoke to the manager Marian, she said they would give us a room but we would have to wait
4pm, came back to the hotel, checked in and they put us in a room on the 7th floor (alleged upgrade) you could see vacuums, water extractors, construction materias everywhere and not a single soul on site.
9:30pm my husband took a shower and there was an overflow, water everywhere (we realized that all the equipment we had seen earlier was due to something similar)
9:30-10p back and forth with front desk we can have someone check it out in the morning we are going to open another room so you can shower there for 30min-1hr you cant use that other room due to sanitary issues just like we suspected, our room was part of the problem.
10:15pm after bickering, once again they offered another hotel and at this time we had no choice. At this time, there were other guests trying to check in but no rooms were available. Rude taxi driver and we got to the other hotel and checked in past 10:45pm. I was able to take a shower there.

To sum this up, this hotel is a scam, they have no respect, they exposed my family to God knows what in a dirty, sewer water infested room and floor and treated us like garbage.

Accor hotels, dont bother apologizing here and twisting my story around, there is no way you can make this up to me because I am never ever booking a room with you. Refund me for my stay.

Please I beg of you, dont book it, its a fraud. See photos

Check in went quickly and smoothly even though there were a couple of people in front of us. The room is basic but airy. If like me, you like sleeping on a firm mattress, you will be disappointed as they are memory foam so quite soft.
Second disappointment was at breakfast time. Many guests had to wait 15 mins to be taken to a table as the restaurant was crowded. Once there, you have to wait again for cups, mugs, juice refill, pastries...
Same scenario on the second day but things got better on the 3rd day.
I didnt bother checkout as the queue was very long and I would have missed my train so I left the keys in the box.
I dont know whether they had a shortage of staff or whether they lacked efficiency but I was not impressed by the waiting staff nor those at reception and not even by the cleaning staff who never greeted us in the corridors unless we did it first.
Sorry, I didnt feel welcome at your hotel!

On business I stayed at this Novotel 2 nites recently
The best Paris experience in the price range
1) 200+ is seldom seen in central Paris
2) 18 Euro for a full buffet breakfast with omelettes waffles cappuccino coffee. Pastries juices etc
3) walk to the Metro
4) 1.2km from the Eiffel Tower
5) dozens of restaurants in walking distance
6) outside the high end tourist area so restaurants were more reasonably priced
7) clean room
8) friendly courteous competent staff

My first choice when I next visit Paris!
